<page api="xb">
      <shortlink>FILE.CREATE_TIME Function</shortlink>
   <topic>FILE.CREATE_TIME Function</topic>
    <description>Returns the date/time at which a file was created</description>
   <prototype static="true">Creation_Time as T = FILE.create_time(C filename )</prototype>
   <arguments>
     <argument>
         <name>filename</name>
         <type>C</type>
         <description>The name of the file.</description>
     </argument>
   </arguments>
  <returns>
      <return>
          <name>Creation_Time</name>
          <types>
              <type>T</type>
          </types>
          <description>Returns the date/time the file was created.</description>
      </return>
  </returns>
   <discussion>
The FILE.CREATE_TIME() method returns the date/time that filename was created. Use the TIME() function to parse out date and time elements from Time.
   </discussion>
   <example code="xb"><![CDATA[
? FILE.create_time("C:\Databases\Help_Database\Help_Database.adb")
= 04/23/2003 08:31:18 70 am   
]]></example>
   
